  question: 'Greetings! I was going to talk about the involvement of a certain god
    in marriages. Yes, as you can probably guess: Zeus. He isn''t exactly the main-god
    of marriage, but he was married to the main-goddess of marriage. So, how about
    this instead. Why do you think Zeus is mentioned in marriages?'
  answers:
  - acceptedAnswer: 1
    answer: Due to his marriage with Hera.
    feedback: Quite possibly, that is part of the reason. But it's mostly because
      of the countless relations he had with all sorts of women. He was in relations
      with countless of gods, and he was even in relations with over a dozen women.
      And not just women, even men. At least that's what I hear, probably just a
      rumour... I mean we Greeks live in modern times, a person's sexual orientation
      certainly doesn't identify them in any social way.
  - acceptedAnswer: 0
    answer: Due to his power over the weather.
    feedback: "Oh, I get it. Because nobody wants bad weather during their wedding.
