      countless relations he had with all sorts of women. And not just women, even
      men. At least that's what I hear, probably just a rumour... I mean we Greeks
      live in modern times, a person's sexual orientation certainly doesn't identify
      them in any social way. To each their own, really\u2026"
  - acceptedAnswer: 1
    answer: Due to his marriages
    feedback: 'Exactly, that is it! He really had countless of lovers: Mnemosyne,
      Leto, Dione, Maia, Semele, Alcmene, Io, Themis, Eurynome, Europa, Metis. And
      those are only a few of the ones I know about. He also had quite a lot of relations
      with mortal women. It makes you wonder...'
